A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 20-2-2096.1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 definitions relative to the "Completion Special Schools Act," so as to lower the age of
3 eligibility from 18 to 16 for certain students to be enrolled in a completion special school;
4 to revise definitions; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
5 purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Code Section 20-2-2096.1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to definitions
9 relative to the "Completion Special Schools Act," is amended by revising paragraphs (5)
10 and (6) as follows:
11 "(5) 'Dropout' means an individual 16 years of age or older who previously dropped out
12 of school according to the uniform definition of 'dropout' provided for in subsection (f)
13 of Code Section 20-14-33.
14 (6) 'Enrollment eligible student' means:
15 (A) An individual 18 16 years of age or older who is eligible for enrollment in
16 appropriate education programs as provided in subsection (a) of Code
